Haven’t made one of these Abstract Painted vases in a while...I’m digging the clashing colours on this one ❤️💚🧡

Quartz Crystal Point .
.
When I saw this quartz point in one of the rock shops last weekend, I knew it needed to be set with a spessartine garnet. The layers that are included in this crystal are amazing. I wish my camera could capture the depth in this stone! The garnet's natural facets bring out the orange inclusions in the quartz. I then added two faceted smoky quartz to bring the piece to the warm, "fall like" side of the color wheel. 🍂
.
.

OG Kush Hash

OG Kush was first cultivated in Florida, in the early ‘90s when a strain from Northern California was crossed with a Hindu Kush plant from Amsterdam. The result was a hybrid with a unique terpene profile that boasts a complex aroma with notes of fuel, skunk, and spice.

The genetic backbone of West Coast cannabis varieties, OG Kush arrived in Los Angeles in 1996 when Matt “Bubba” Berger brought it (along with “The Bubba,” which was later used to create the famed Bubba Kush) from Florida to legendary cultivator Josh D. Since then, OG Kush has become a worldwide staple used to create numerous famous strains like GSC and Headband. There are many different phenotypes of OG Kush, including Tahoe OG, SFV OG, and Ghost OG. (@leafly)
